  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "6. For—a mere particle of transition here [Tholuck], like \"but\" or \"now.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to be carnally minded—literally, \"the mind\" or \"minding of the flesh\" (Margin); that is, the pursuit of fleshly ends.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "is death—not only \"ends in\" [Alford, &c.], but even now \"is\"; carrying death into its bosom, so that such are \"dead while they live\" (1Ti 5:6; Eph 2:1, 5) [Philippi].",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but to be spiritually minded—\"the mind\" or \"minding of the spirit\"; that is, the pursuit of spiritual objects.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "is life and peace—not \"life\" only, in contrast with the \"death\" that is in the other pursuit, but \"peace\"; it is the very element of the soul's deepest repose and true bliss.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
