      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " itself that is intended to be conveyed, and that indeed, in accordance with the prevailing concrete mode of description, as a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "conscious",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " effort, a real ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "φρονεῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not as an ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "impulse",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that makes the Ego its captive (Hofmann), since the same predicate ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "φρόνημα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " applies to the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "σάρξ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as well as to the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πνεῦμα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". On ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰρήνη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "blessedness",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 2:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Understood in the narrower sense (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "peace",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " with God), it would yield a hysteronproteron, which Fritzsche actually assumes.",
        "children": []
      },
